Hard to understand but has good slides and is a fair grader as well as fair when dealing with students. Course was difficult but with effort it is interesting material that is easy to grasp. Solid prof and decent course. Beware the midterm was more tough than the final.
Stay with his weekly lectures, he is a great prof
stay with his weekly programs. He is great, but you need to read the textbook if u want A
Good prof, would recommend to all

I had Octavian for 1102 and 2117, he's a great professor as well as person. Super helpful and has real world experience when it comes to development economics. His lectures are just fine, and his midterms and finals are straightforward. Super approachable and intelligent. Sad to see his contract expire after Winter 2016.

Took his first year Macro class purely because i hate the auditorium classroom that David Gray teaches in. Surprisingly, he's a great prof! I love his accent and his midterm is super straight forward. As for his 2 assignments, unless you're writing about something totally irrelevant, he'll definitely try to give u a good mark. Read the textbook tho
His slides are clear and easy to follow, his accent is amazing and he's a pretty easy marker. I recommend him!

This course is an easy A, the textbook can be found online in PDF version and is correlated basically word for word to the slides so if you skip class it doesn't matter too much as long as you read and understand the chapters in the textbook. There are 4 assignments, a midterm and a final, all of which are easy if you have done the reading.
Good professor, clear lectures, 1midterm and 1final with 4assignments (he rarely ever gives anybody 0). Fair grading, appreciated and learned a lot from this course.
Was an awesome prof but 8:30 am lectures just weren't for me. Course gets content heavy so focus is important!

Really liked his class, he is a GREAT prof. His tests/assignments are not hard as long as you use the study guide and keep up as you go along!! His accent is thick, but not hard to understand. He is funny and makes early morning classes not dreadful to go to.
His lectures are fun and he tried to have the class participate even though we were a big group. He answers questions and he will be happy to help you if you go to his office hours.
He's a great prof!

I recommend Octavian to anyone taking Macro! He is so passionate about it and is adorable with his jokes. I personally love macroeconomics, but it is a tough class so be sure to do your readings and pay attention. Would take again!
Very clear lecture notes. Sweet prof. Do the suggested exercises!

Very easy to learn from and a calm demeanour that helps with studying such a boring topic. His grading scheme is very minimal work wise so make sure you do well on the midterm. Would not recommend taking if you don't like development as it is heavily emphasized on third world countries with a mild focus on the economics of development. Easy Course!
Awesome lectures tough tests do the suggested work he gives!
Economics is not my strong point but he is always very engaging and entertaining! DO THE SUGGESTED TEXTBOOK WORK! It helps so much!

Lots of homework. Lots to read. Lots to study. Exams are not easy. If you don't study and follow his weekly program, you won't get a good grade! I found him helpful when you are ready to discuss and lectures are interesting.

He really knows his stuff. He is willing to answer all sort of questions during office hours even those he has already addressed during class. He is so sweet. Definitely would take another course with him.
He's a great prof! Really seems passionate of economics! His lecture slides are also nice and clear.  Very expensive textbook, not all that necessary in my opinion.
